title: For Trade:  Special Weapons SW760 (S&W 76; Carl Gustav M45); unfired
postcontent:
I am selling looking to trade an unfired Special Weapons SW760 semi-automatic rifle in like-new condition. Included are five stock 36-round magazines and the new-manufacture spare parts (including a spare firing pin) shown in photos below. The barrel is quick-detach and the stock folds. 

I am only looking to trade face-to-face.

This SW760 comes with a legal 16" barrel, but 8" barrels are available (e.g., an 8" Suomi M31 barrel fits) and can used if you are willing to pay the appropriate one-time $200 tax to the ATF. Also, Suomi M31 36-rd magazines can be adapted for use with this rifle. 

A bit of history: This is a semi-auto clone of the Vietnam-era Smith & Wesson S&W 76 submachine gun, which, in turn, was a clone of the Carl Gustav M45 submachine gun (AKA the "Swedish K"). The SW760 and its predecessors are all chambered in 9mm. The seals of the Vietnam era wanted to purchase the M45 from Sweden (if only because it would fire straight out of the water), but the Swedish government said "no." S&W then agreed to build a clone for the US military. Ironically, the S&W 76 went into production shortly after the Vietnam War ended.
